* change directory into the project you want to enable Gulp.
* run the command: $ npm init. This will create a file named "package.json" under the 
  project root.
* run the command: $ npm install --save-dev gulp. This installs Gulp locally and save
  this dependency info into the package.json file. 
* run the command: $ npm install --save-dev gulp-util. This installs the Gulp utility.
* create a file named "gulpfile.js" under the project root.
* run the command: $ npm install --save-dev gulp-livereload. This installs the live 
  reload module.
